==English==

===Etymology===
Medieval English ''[[preist]]'' < Old English ''[[prēost]]''

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:SAMPA|SAMPA]]: /'pr\i:st/
*[[w:IPA|IPA]]: /'pɻiːst/
*{{audio|en-us-priest.ogg|Audio (US)}}
*Rhymes: [[Rhymes:English:-iːst|-iːst]]

===Noun===
'''priest''' (''plural:'' [[priests]])

# a religious [[clergyman]] who is trained to perform services or [[sacrifice]]s at a church or temple.
#: ''The priest at the [[Catholic]] [[church]] heard his [[confession]]''.
#: ''The [[Shinto]] priest burnt [[incense]] for his [[ancestors]]''.
#: ''The israelite priests of [[Yahweh]]’s temple were descended from [[Moses]]' brother [[Aaron]]''.
# a blunt tool, used for stunning and killing fish

